Source: Te Waimate
Author: STUDHOLME
Vol / Page: 167
Edition: 1954
Quote: From the time the land was taken up in the fifties until about 1860 might be described as the `man power' period of farming; the only implements available were spades, shovels, picks, hoes, scythes, sickles, and flails, the last named commonly known as `The Irish Combine.'
